race.description: Computer Talk - Business It Experts Hcp (Bm66)
race.comment: SILVER MAGNATE (2) has been turned over at very short odds his past two since a strong win first up but has been tested up in class and just gave relatively good horses too big a start last time at Flemington. Comes back a couple of grades now and while drawn to get back, he is still very lightly raced and the big track will suit. SIESTA (16) is coming along nicely. The maiden win fresh was good and she measured up well to this level last time behind a progressive horse in Enamorada. Tipping that form holds up nicely. ENNA'S DREAM (4) is a consistent mare who continues to race well this time in. Up to 1400m now holds no fears and she should get every chance from the cushy draw. Not sure what to do with KIRRIBILLI (8) who was awful first up at Sandown Hillside. Her best figures would just about win this and she's been given time to bounce back. Watch the market. IL CUBO (3) is an each-way hope again.
